channel.title: .swf to excel
channel.description: Does anyone know how i can download this http://www.kongregate.com/games/pixelate/mr-bounce onto an excel file? or at the very least on to my computer so that i can play it?

item.title: .swf to excel
item.dc:creator: @sanga282 sanga282
item.description:
@sanga282 wrote:

[quote=“kloplop321, post:2, topic:211107”]that is a semi-cool game actually. but I would highly recommend getting a plugin that will show you the html AFTER the JavaScript execution.
EDIT
There I figured it out
http://a.kongregate.com/games/pixelate/mr-bounce/frame/1212982488065?user_id=&username=Guest
and if that random number does not work in there, put this in another tab “javascript:new Date().getTime();” and press enter, then copy and replace the number in that and it should work. You can’t hide a flash file

Also you can do Ctrl+S when it loads to save it.[/quote]
thanks for the help much appreciated
